definitions.definition: ( US , historical ) A member of a section of the Democratic-Republican Party between 1805 and 1811, following John Randolph of Roanoke . (From tertium quid .)
Paired with quo , in reference to the phrase quid pro quo ( “ this for that ” ) : something offered in exchange for something else.

secondary_definitions: ( US , historical ) A member of a section of the Democratic-Republican Party between 1805 and 1811, following John Randolph of Roanoke . (From tertium quid .)

definitions.definition: ( historical ) A sovereign or guinea , that is, a certain coin or amount of money.
( UK , colloquial ) Pound sterling . ( usually only used with a whole number of pounds )
examples: Seven quid for a toastie? You're joking, aren't you?!

definitions.definition: ( Ireland , Commonwealth , colloquial , historical ) Various national currencies typically known by the name " pound ".
( Commonwealth , colloquial , by extension , rare ) Dollar , dollars .

definitions.definition: A piece of material for chewing , especially chewing tobacco .
The act of chewing such tobacco.
